in none of that no more.

247
00:23:07,855 --> 00:23:09,525
What, that the lions
didn't eat him?

248
00:23:09,627 --> 00:23:11,860
Nah. I don't believe
in none of it.

249
00:23:15,670 --> 00:23:18,602
I used to go
to these prison chapel
meetings sometimes.

250
00:23:18,704 --> 00:23:20,899
An old white-haired preacher,
a bunch of outlaws

251
00:23:21,001 --> 00:23:23,107
sittin' in all
these folding chairs,

252
00:23:23,209 --> 00:23:25,775
yelling their hallelujahs.

253
00:23:27,645 --> 00:23:30,314
Preacher'd get up,
give his sermon.

254
00:23:30,416 --> 00:23:31,781
And everybody get
to take turns,

255
00:23:31,883 --> 00:23:34,351
getting up at the pulpit,
give their testimonies.

256
00:23:34,453 --> 00:23:36,817
"Yes, I stole."
"Yes, I raped."

257
00:23:36,920 --> 00:23:40,588
"Yes, I beat the shit
out of my fellow man."

258
00:23:40,690 --> 00:23:42,456
"But now I found
the love of God,

259
00:23:42,558 --> 00:23:44,293
now I see the light."

260
00:23:44,395 --> 00:23:45,793
And so on, and so on,

261
00:23:45,896 --> 00:23:48,127
and all their clappings
and "amens," and shit,

262
00:23:48,229 --> 00:23:51,230
and I just didn't care
for it, so I stopped going.

263
00:23:51,332 --> 00:23:52,769
Hmm.

264
00:23:55,439 --> 00:23:56,603
Do you think it's fair?

265
00:23:56,705 --> 00:23:58,777
What? Do I think
what's fair?

266
00:23:58,879 --> 00:23:59,777
Tsk...

267
00:24:00,680 --> 00:24:03,411
Well, that man can get
into the magic Kingdom

268
00:24:03,513 --> 00:24:05,878
no matter what they done,

269
00:24:05,980 --> 00:24:08,488
as long as they say
the magic words.

270
00:24:09,521 --> 00:24:11,756
Words have power
if you mean them.

271
00:24:12,859 --> 00:24:16,994
And it doesn't matter
what you and me think
is fair.

272
00:24:17,096 --> 00:24:18,495
This Good Book

273
00:24:18,597 --> 00:24:20,962
tells me that the door
is always open.

274
00:24:22,235 --> 00:24:23,333
Let me ask you something.

275
00:24:23,436 --> 00:24:25,238
How's what you did
different?

276
00:24:25,340 --> 00:24:28,233
'Cause I made
one big fucking mistake!

277
00:24:29,575 --> 00:24:30,935
And I didn't mean it.
They meant it.

278
00:24:31,037 --> 00:24:33,806
Damn right.
And you ain't them.

279
00:24:33,908 --> 00:24:36,347
You made
a big fucking mistake

280
00:24:36,449 --> 00:24:38,280
and you did
your time for it.

281
00:24:38,382 --> 00:24:40,179
Well, in whose eyes?

282
00:24:41,648 --> 00:24:44,689
Mine? Theirs?

283
00:24:45,657 --> 00:24:47,788
I have an accident,
I get swooped away

284
00:24:47,890 --> 00:24:49,558
and locked away
behind these bars.

285
00:24:49,660 --> 00:24:50,923
Don't get to show
my remorse,

286
00:24:51,025 --> 00:24:52,992
get my sorrys
to nobody that I hurt.

287
00:24:53,094 --> 00:24:56,202
Ain't you, ain't me,
ain't nobody out there

288
00:24:56,304 --> 00:24:58,734
just gonna snap
their fingers

289
00:24:58,837 --> 00:25:02,135
and instill some sort
of forgiveness in me.

290
00:25:03,304 --> 00:25:06,579
Son, you're being
awful damn hard
on yourself.

291
00:25:10,077 --> 00:25:13,585
I got to believe
we can be forgiven.

292
00:25:13,687 --> 00:25:16,754
'Cause if we can't, well,
then we're all fucked.

293
00:25:21,293 --> 00:25:22,322
[Mitchell chuckles]

294
00:25:23,358 --> 00:25:25,992
It was them boys that did
that to your face,
wasn't it?

295
00:25:26,094 --> 00:25:28,330
Waitin' at the bus stop,
soon as I pulled in.

296
00:25:28,432 --> 00:25:31,202
Yeah, fuckin' Larry.

297
00:25:31,304 --> 00:25:34,099
Got you set up
at, uh,

298
00:25:34,201 --> 00:25:38,204
one of my places there
at, uh, Michigan Avenue.

299
00:25:38,306 --> 00:25:40,175
Here's your car keys,
got the keys to the place--

300
00:25:40,277 --> 00:25:42,545
It's that old place
we put the shutters on,
you remember?

301
00:25:42,647 --> 00:25:44,178
Oh, I know.
How could I forget?

302
00:25:44,280 --> 00:25:47,145
Yeah, but, uh, listen,
why don't you
just stay out here,

303
00:25:47,248 --> 00:25:49,653
you give those fellas
some time to cool off?

304
00:25:49,756 --> 00:25:51,852
Oh, they ain't
coolin' off
any time soon.

305
00:25:51,954 --> 00:25:53,351
'Sides, they know
where you live.

306
00:25:53,453 --> 00:25:56,959
They can pull up the driveway
just as easy as I can.

307
00:25:58,124 --> 00:26:00,061
I ain't bringin' that
out here.

308
00:26:02,099 --> 00:26:04,637
Well, I've got
something for you.
Hang on to these.

309
00:26:14,279 --> 00:26:16,143
Here. [sighs]

310
00:26:18,713 --> 00:26:23,120
I don't recall anything
about no hunting rifle
in the New Testament.

311
00:26:23,222 --> 00:26:27,352
Well, you can only turn
so many cheeks,
and I only got four, so...

312
00:26:27,454 --> 00:26:31,762
I'd be breaking
about two dozen laws
just by having it.

313
00:26:31,864 --> 00:26:33,560
I'd feel a whole lot better
knowing you're safe.

314
00:26:33,662 --> 00:26:37,230
- Ain't gon' be that bad.
- Well, you don't know
how it's gonna get.

315
00:26:41,404 --> 00:26:42,873
Okay.

316
00:26:44,838 --> 00:26:47,240
[soft music playing]

317
00:26:47,342 --> 00:26:49,781
[Russell]<i> Do you ever think</i>
<i>about that moment?</i>

318
00:26:51,477 --> 00:26:53,912
<i>That moment I got</i>
<i>a little too big, too old,</i>

319
00:26:54,014 --> 00:26:55,679
<i>too heavy for you to carry?</i>

320
00:26:55,782 --> 00:27:00,220
<i>You think to yourself,</i>
<i>"Goddamn! I can't carry</i>
<i>my son no more."</i>

321
00:27:03,291 --> 00:27:05,591
<i>You don't have to carry me</i>
<i>no more, Dad.</i>

322
00:27:05,693 --> 00:27:06,758
[bag thuds]

323
00:27:06,860 --> 00:27:09,097
<i>I'll be okay.</i>

324
00:27:24,411 --> 00:27:26,851
- [door bell jingles]
- [indistinct chatter]

325
00:27:45,935 --> 00:27:48,774
- [waitress indistinct]
- Thank you.

326
00:27:50,607 --> 00:27:52,041
Shot of Bug, please.

327
00:27:53,379 --> 00:27:54,747
[pool balls clatter]

328
00:27:57,683 --> 00:27:59,279
- [whooping]
- [bottles clinking]

329
00:28:04,851 --> 00:28:06,418
[laughter]

330
00:28:13,531 --> 00:28:16,428
[muffled screaming]

331
00:28:22,342 --> 00:28:24,370
[breathing heavily]

332
00:28:26,142 --> 00:28:28,374
- [insects chirping]
- [soft music continues]

333
00:29:43,818 --> 00:29:45,088
[siren whoops]

334
00:29:50,391 --> 00:29:52,997
Get out of the truck!
Show me your hands!

335
00:30:00,207 --> 00:30:01,973
Slowly.

336
00:30:09,444 --> 00:30:13,283
Get that goddamn thing
out of my face, Boyd!

337
00:30:13,386 --> 00:30:14,617
[laughing]

338
00:30:14,719 --> 00:30:16,588
Well, I'll be damned!

339
00:30:16,690 --> 00:30:18,050
- When'd you get home?
- Noon.

340
00:30:18,153 --> 00:30:20,385
- Noon today?
- Noon today.

341
00:30:20,487 --> 00:30:22,187
Give me some love, man.
Don't stand there.

342
00:30:22,289 --> 00:30:23,690
- All right.
- [both grunting]

343
00:30:23,792 --> 00:30:25,293
[both chuckling]

344
00:30:27,696 --> 00:30:29,165
Stop it.

345
00:30:29,267 --> 00:30:31,129
We grown now. You can't be
lifting me up like that.

346
00:30:31,232 --> 00:30:33,671
- Oh, I got you.
- [Boyd laughs]

347
00:30:33,773 --> 00:30:35,633
Well, talk to me.
How was it?

348
00:30:35,735 --> 00:30:39,945
About what you can imagine,
'cept way fucking worse.

349
00:30:42,146 --> 00:30:44,848
How's Lacey? She still
turning backflips?

350
00:30:44,950 --> 00:30:46,444
God no! She couldn't put
her right leg

351
00:30:46,547 --> 00:30:48,748
in that old cheerleader
outfit if she wanted to.

352
00:30:48,850 --> 00:30:50,184
[both laugh]

353
00:30:50,286 --> 00:30:52,386
You gotta love her,
though, man. You got to.

354
00:30:53,956 --> 00:30:55,486
So what's goin' on here?

355
00:30:55,588 --> 00:30:58,563
[Boyd] Ain't no point
in keeping it a secret.

356
00:30:58,665 --> 00:30:59,962
Be on the news
tomorrow.

357
00:31:00,064 --> 00:31:02,094
One of our own shot
with his own pistol,

358
00:31:02,197 --> 00:31:03,701
which we can't seem
to find.

359
00:31:03,803 --> 00:31:06,535
- Shit.
- [distant train horn]

360
00:31:06,637 --> 00:31:07,905
Anyone I know?

361
00:31:08,008 --> 00:31:10,738
Nah, this guy came down
from Tupelo or somewhere

362
00:31:10,840 --> 00:31:12,143
a year or two back.

363
00:31:12,912 --> 00:31:14,643
Been on thin ice
ever since he got here.

364
00:31:14,745 --> 00:31:18,180
So I wouldn't be surprised
if something ain't catch
back up to his ass.

365
00:31:18,282 --> 00:31:20,478
Just hate for Lacey
to find out about this one.

366
00:31:20,580 --> 00:31:23,254
She stays worried enough
about me, you know?

367
00:31:23,357 --> 00:31:24,550
Oh, I bet.

368
00:31:24,652 --> 00:31:27,925
Well, they're gonna ask me
if I checked you out, so...

369
00:31:28,027 --> 00:31:30,056
I gotta check you out,
see what's in the truck.

370
00:31:30,158 --> 00:31:32,492
Okay, yeah.
Open it up.

371
00:31:42,842 --> 00:31:45,143
Russ, you ain't been out
24 hours.

372
00:31:45,245 --> 00:31:48,207
Shit, man! You know
you ain't supposed
to have no gun.

373
00:31:48,309 --> 00:31:50,980
Just got out
of the damn cage, Boyd.

374
00:31:51,082 --> 00:31:52,444
You don't know
what that feels like.

375
00:31:52,546 --> 00:31:54,653
- You wanna go back
to the cage?
- No.

376
00:31:54,755 --> 00:31:56,150
Didn't think so,
so if I was you,

377
00:31:56,252 --> 00:31:58,056
get in the truck
and call it a night.

378
00:32:00,955 --> 00:32:02,357
Yes, officer.

379
00:32:06,865 --> 00:32:10,101
[suspenseful music playing]

380
00:32:19,041 --> 00:32:20,375
[Brenda]<i> This is it.</i>

381
00:32:21,816 --> 00:32:24,209
You have the whole place
to yourselves.

382
00:32:24,311 --> 00:32:26,611
The doors lock
at 8 p.m.

383
00:32:26,713 --> 00:32:29,286
If you go out,
you need a password
to get in.

384
00:32:29,388 --> 00:32:32,285
Oh, hey, you wait.
You let me help you
get up there.

385
00:32:32,387 --> 00:32:33,853
Well, let me help
put your bags away.

386
00:32:33,955 --> 00:32:36,424
No. We're good.

387
00:32:38,366 --> 00:32:39,326
Is, uh...

388
00:32:39,428 --> 00:32:40,964
Is there anything
I can do for-for work?

389
00:32:41,066 --> 00:32:42,359
I mean, I'll do
just about anything.

390
00:32:42,461 --> 00:32:44,400
There's a bar
up the road

391
00:32:44,502 --> 00:32:46,799
where you can help
with the dishes
and work in the kitchen.

392
00:32:46,901 --> 00:32:50,702
Now, it ain't much,
but he pays out
at the end of the day.

393
00:32:52,711 --> 00:32:55,010
Can I work today?

394
00:32:55,112 --> 00:32:56,677
You look
like you need a break.

395
00:32:56,779 --> 00:32:58,347
I don't.

396
00:32:59,215 --> 00:33:01,551
You sure nobody's
following you?

397
00:33:01,653 --> 00:33:03,484
We get that.

398
00:33:06,325 --> 00:33:08,754
Didn't you tell her
that she could have
a hot dog?

399
00:33:08,856 --> 00:33:09,820
Hmm?

400
00:33:10,656 --> 00:33:13,131
- You want a hot dog?
- Come on, baby.

401
00:33:28,110 --> 00:33:31,347
[somber music playing]

402
00:33:38,954 --> 00:33:40,686
[birds chirping]

403
00:33:57,674 --> 00:34:01,275
Sometimes I have a hard time
remembering how old he'd be.

404
00:34:01,377 --> 00:34:04,549
I ride by here
just to remind myself.

405
00:34:04,651 --> 00:34:05,849
You ever do that?

406
00:34:05,951 --> 00:34:08,247
I could say
at anytime...

407
00:34:08,349 --> 00:34:11,383
exactly how old
he'd be.

408
00:34:11,485 --> 00:34:13,692
Twenty-five years,
three months.

409
00:34:13,794 --> 00:34:16,194
Yeah, I wish
I could do that.

410
00:34:18,027 --> 00:34:19,491
It's all right.

411
00:34:19,593 --> 00:34:23,668
You got a busy life,
you got a family.

412
00:34:23,770 --> 00:34:25,401
Ain't nobody blamin' you.

413
00:34:27,637 --> 00:34:31,572
Besides...
I remember enough
for the both of us.

414
00:34:39,347 --> 00:34:42,083
Why do you always
do that?

415
00:34:42,186 --> 00:34:46,224
His toll.
To bring him home.

416
00:34:48,324 --> 00:34:50,558
There's always
a price to pay.

417
00:35:01,036 --> 00:35:03,340
I like that.

418
00:35:07,614 --> 00:35:10,140
[laughing]

419
00:35:10,242 --> 00:35:13,719
Man, it's no wonder
these boys are stacked
like brick houses,

420
00:35:13,821 --> 00:35:14,786
you feedin' them like that.

421
00:35:14,888 --> 00:35:16,080
Well, they're hearty eaters.

422
00:35:16,182 --> 00:35:17,420
Boys...

423
00:35:18,453 --> 00:35:20,823
Well, I thank you
much, Lacey.

424
00:35:20,925 --> 00:35:21,826
That was damn good.

425
00:35:21,928 --> 00:35:23,555
We're just glad
you're home.

426
00:35:23,657 --> 00:35:25,957
I'm just glad these boys
took after you.

427
00:35:26,059 --> 00:35:29,828
- [laughs] Your mouth
to God's ears.
- [Boyd] Hey, now.

428
00:35:33,006 --> 00:35:34,803
Oh, I see
you're up to mischief.

429
00:35:34,905 --> 00:35:36,238
[glasses clink]

430
00:35:36,340 --> 00:35:38,206
- 'Bout that time?
- [dishes rattling]

431
00:35:38,308 --> 00:35:40,677
Don't act
like you don't know.

432
00:35:40,779 --> 00:35:41,906
[Boyd sighs]

433
00:35:59,258 --> 00:36:01,927
Why the hell
you didn't call me
knowing you was getting out?

434
00:36:02,029 --> 00:36:03,367
Hmm?

435
00:36:03,469 --> 00:36:05,930
You know I would've drove
down there and got you.

436
00:36:07,601 --> 00:36:09,707
You know it don't work
like that.

437
00:36:09,809 --> 00:36:11,809
Tsk, see, uh...

438
00:36:11,911 --> 00:36:13,371
that's where you're wrong.

439
00:36:13,473 --> 00:36:15,142
I got special privileges.

440
00:36:15,244 --> 00:36:17,780
Flash 'em the old badge.

441
00:36:17,882 --> 00:36:20,352
[both laughing]

442
00:36:20,454 --> 00:36:22,721
- Special privileges.
- Well, I'll just
show 'em mine.

443
00:36:22,823 --> 00:36:24,121
That didn't work
anyways.

444
00:36:24,223 --> 00:36:25,483
- And it's bigger.
- [Boyd laughing]

445
00:36:25,586 --> 00:36:28,527
Always has been,
always will be.

446
00:36:28,629 --> 00:36:31,155
[chuckling]

447
00:36:31,258 --> 00:36:32,693
All fools.

448
00:36:35,165 --> 00:36:37,665
Tsk. Larry had it figured.

449
00:36:39,502 --> 00:36:41,506
That's what happened
to your face?

450
00:36:41,608 --> 00:36:42,703
Sure is.

451
00:36:43,539 --> 00:36:45,374
How serious do you think
the brothers are?

452
00:36:45,477 --> 00:36:48,411
Oh, I don't know
how serious they are
together.

453
00:36:48,513 --> 00:36:50,876
I know Larry's
pretty serious
all on his own.

454
00:36:52,547 --> 00:36:53,745
You want me to go
say something?

455
00:36:53,847 --> 00:36:55,552
- 'Cause you know I will.
- No. Shit, no.

456
00:36:55,654 --> 00:36:57,818
I've dealt with way worse
since the last time
I saw you.

457
00:36:57,920 --> 00:37:00,822
Besides, Larry's
just a puppy dog,
comparatively speaking.

458
00:37:00,924 --> 00:37:04,323
Yeah, an aggravating,
chew-up-your-shit
puppy dog, though.

459
00:37:04,425 --> 00:37:06,590
There's a big difference.

460
00:37:06,692 --> 00:37:08,300
[grunts]
Well, you know...

461
00:37:11,797 --> 00:37:13,868
How you doin'?
You doin' okay?

462
00:37:13,971 --> 00:37:15,604
Doing good.

463
00:37:18,008 --> 00:37:19,910
Russ, come on.

464
00:37:20,012 --> 00:37:21,577
How you really doin'?

465
00:37:23,777 --> 00:37:25,512
Thought I'd feel
a little different.

466
00:37:25,614 --> 00:37:28,686
Feels good
all at the same time, but...

467
00:37:28,788 --> 00:37:30,953
I don't know.

468
00:37:31,055 --> 00:37:32,423
You seen her yet?

469
00:37:33,188 --> 00:37:34,722
No, not yet.

470
00:37:35,489 --> 00:37:36,689
But it's a small town,

471
00:37:36,791 --> 00:37:39,929
I'm bound to run into her
sooner or later.

472
00:37:40,031 --> 00:37:42,293
[chuckles] Man...

473
00:37:42,395 --> 00:37:47,067
We burned up a lot of miles
and a lot of time
out on those roads.

474
00:37:47,169 --> 00:37:48,472
I missed that.

475
00:37:50,572 --> 00:37:52,339
Turns out,
I missed you too, bro.

476
00:37:52,441 --> 00:37:55,875
Oh, don't get
all gushy on me.

477
00:37:58,446 --> 00:38:00,016
I missed you too,
bud.

478
00:38:00,118 --> 00:38:02,849
I knew it.
I knew it.

479
00:38:05,485 --> 00:38:07,392
[insects chirping]

480
00:38:12,862 --> 00:38:16,632
- [suspenseful music playing]
- [tapping on flask]

481
00:38:42,488 --> 00:38:43,725
[cuts engine]

482
00:39:23,597 --> 00:39:24,964
[curtain rings rattle]

483
00:39:46,420 --> 00:39:47,723
[light thud]

484
00:40:02,504 --> 00:40:05,741
[tense music playing]

485
00:40:14,481 --> 00:40:16,081
[birds chirping]

486
00:40:26,097 --> 00:40:27,532
[door creaks]

487
00:40:37,510 --> 00:40:40,275
[Russell]<i> How long</i>
<i>have you been here?</i>

488
00:40:40,377 --> 00:40:41,645
[Sarah]<i> All morning.</i>

489
00:40:42,713 --> 00:40:44,945
<i>Hadn't gotten up</i>
<i>the courage to knock.</i>

490
00:40:46,613 --> 00:40:48,581
You look the same.

491
00:40:48,684 --> 00:40:51,754
- [laughs] Please.
- You do.

492
00:40:53,021 --> 00:40:56,693
Well... you look like
you could use a hot meal.

493
00:40:57,925 --> 00:40:59,793
You know, people
keep saying that to me,

494
00:40:59,895 --> 00:41:02,363
but nobody's offered
to buy me any dinner.

495
00:41:02,465 --> 00:41:04,030
[Sarah chuckles softly]

496
00:41:06,632 --> 00:41:08,639
You all right?

497
00:41:11,538 --> 00:41:13,578
Yeah, I'm okay.

498
00:41:15,474 --> 00:41:16,647
You?

499
00:41:17,677 --> 00:41:20,984
[sighs] Oh, yes.

500
00:41:21,086 --> 00:41:22,752
I'm all right.

501
00:41:28,120 --> 00:41:30,892
I bet your daddy's happy
that you're home.

502
00:41:33,564 --> 00:41:35,327
I was sorry
about your mama.

503
00:41:35,429 --> 00:41:37,261
Yeah...

504
00:41:38,864 --> 00:41:41,804
[sniffles] Yeah, boy.

505
00:41:41,906 --> 00:41:44,939
Sure would've been nice
for her to see me make it.

506
00:41:48,180 --> 00:41:50,582
I bet she's smiling.

507
00:41:56,616 --> 00:41:58,183
Remodeling?

508
00:41:59,786 --> 00:42:02,191
Hurricane last night.

509
00:42:02,293 --> 00:42:03,755
[laughing] I bet.

510
00:42:03,857 --> 00:42:05,458
That hurricane
got a name?

511
00:42:05,560 --> 00:42:07,062
Oh, they usually do.

512
00:42:07,165 --> 00:42:08,325
[chuckles]

513
00:42:17,903 --> 00:42:19,809
You still mad
at me?

514
00:42:21,646 --> 00:42:23,879
I told you then
like I'll tell you now.

515
00:42:25,285 --> 00:42:27,586
Ain't nothing
to be mad about.

516
00:42:30,820 --> 00:42:33,218
Seems like you told me
the same thing.

517
00:42:34,687 --> 00:42:35,957
I knows it.

518
00:42:37,691 --> 00:42:39,928
I just wondered.

519
00:42:42,065 --> 00:42:45,637
I'm the one that told you
to stop coming to see me.

520
00:42:47,671 --> 00:42:49,839
But I'm the one
who agreed.

521
00:42:59,184 --> 00:43:00,982
How many kids?

522
00:43:02,016 --> 00:43:05,252
I got twin boys
and a little girl.

523
00:43:05,354 --> 00:43:06,790
How old?

524
00:43:08,825 --> 00:43:12,631
My boys are four
and the girl is two.

525
00:43:23,007 --> 00:43:26,403
Man, all I want to do
is hold your hand right now.

526
00:43:27,840 --> 00:43:29,648
Just for one minute.

527
00:43:37,719 --> 00:43:39,955
[melancholy music playing]

528
00:43:42,260 --> 00:43:43,354
[Sarah sniffles]

529
00:43:48,694 --> 00:43:49,965
[kisses]

530
00:43:53,832 --> 00:43:55,740
[Sarah sobbing]

531
00:44:21,898 --> 00:44:24,769
There's a whole lot
between us now.

532
00:44:28,275 --> 00:44:30,104
[sighs] A whole lot...

533
00:44:36,548 --> 00:44:38,783
I can't keep it
anymore.

534
00:44:40,252 --> 00:44:42,050
But it's yours.

535
00:44:43,617 --> 00:44:45,350
It was.

536
00:44:46,755 --> 00:44:49,019
[sniffles]
I gotta go.

537
00:44:49,121 --> 00:44:52,357
[melancholic music continues]

538
00:45:05,937 --> 00:45:07,438
[dishes clatter]

539
00:45:24,891 --> 00:45:28,129
[soft music playing]

540
00:45:37,408 --> 00:45:38,843
[Maben] Hello.

541
00:45:39,610 --> 00:45:42,173
- Mommy!
- [laughs]

542
00:45:42,275 --> 00:45:45,509
Hi, baby. Thank you
for watching her.

543
00:45:46,884 --> 00:45:48,881
- What are you doing?
- Coloring.

544
00:45:48,983 --> 00:45:50,783
Red? Too scary.
Too scary.

545
00:45:50,885 --> 00:45:52,489
- Purple!
- Yeah!

546
00:45:52,591 --> 00:45:55,492
Purple, a really
nice light...

547
00:45:55,594 --> 00:45:58,561
- shade of purple.
- Yeah.

548
00:45:58,663 --> 00:46:00,359
[Analee]<i> Tell me about Daddy.</i>

549
00:46:03,763 --> 00:46:05,067
Well...

550
00:46:06,537 --> 00:46:07,767
<i>You have his eyes.</i>

551
00:46:07,869 --> 00:46:10,502
<i>- I do?</i>
<i>- Mm-hmm.</i>

552
00:46:10,604 --> 00:46:16,373
<i>And he would've been</i>
<i>able to make you</i>
<i>laugh so hard</i>

553
00:46:16,475 --> 00:46:19,876
<i>that I think</i>
<i>you would've broken ribs.</i>

554
00:46:19,978 --> 00:46:21,545
[Maben chuckles]

555
00:46:23,653 --> 00:46:25,384
<i>And he was just...</i>

556
00:46:26,621 --> 00:46:28,827
so real.

557
00:46:29,625 --> 00:46:31,357
And so kind.

558
00:46:33,159 --> 00:46:35,394
<i>And he was my first everything.</i>

559
00:46:38,669 --> 00:46:40,531
And together
we made you.

560
00:46:42,638 --> 00:46:44,734
And you're...

561
00:46:44,836 --> 00:46:48,275
the most important thing
in the whole world,
do you know that?

562
00:46:51,381 --> 00:46:52,543
Hmm?

563
00:46:59,788 --> 00:47:02,025
[soft music playing]

564
00:47:06,197 --> 00:47:08,792
- Analee... Analee,
where's our stuff?
- Yeah?

565
00:47:08,895 --> 00:47:10,462
In there?

566
00:47:13,772 --> 00:47:14,903
Who told you
to empty the bag?

567
00:47:15,005 --> 00:47:17,337
I-I-I didn't do it.
The lady did.

568
00:47:18,607 --> 00:47:20,307
[gasps]

569
00:47:21,276 --> 00:47:24,081
- Get on your shoes.
- [stammering] What for?

570
00:47:24,183 --> 00:47:27,583
Do what I say
and put your shoes on
and get your stuff.

571
00:47:27,685 --> 00:47:29,016
But I don't wanna go!

572
00:47:29,118 --> 00:47:31,855
Baby, shh! I know
you wanna stay here,

573
00:47:31,957 --> 00:47:34,388
- but we gotta go.
- W-what's happening?

574
00:47:34,490 --> 00:47:37,124
Just listen to me.
Do what I say
and put your shoes on.

575
00:47:37,226 --> 00:47:38,756
And get the rest
of your stuff over there.

576
00:47:38,858 --> 00:47:40,963
- You said we could
stop walking...
- I know what I said.

577
00:47:41,065 --> 00:47:43,594
- ...once we got
to Mississippi--
- Hey! Baby!

578
00:47:43,696 --> 00:47:46,432
Look at me. I love you.
I'm gonna take care of you,

579
00:47:46,534 --> 00:47:48,767
but you gotta do
what I'm telling you
to do right now.

580
00:47:48,869 --> 00:47:50,601
Do you get it?

581
00:47:52,274 --> 00:47:54,209
- Mommy, where are we going?
- [shushes]

582
00:47:55,514 --> 00:47:57,410
I want my crayons.

583
00:47:59,077 --> 00:48:00,512
- Mommy!
- Shh!

584
00:48:06,626 --> 00:48:08,223
[whispering]
Okay, this way.

585
00:48:09,994 --> 00:48:13,426
Okay. Now you have
to be so quiet.

586
00:48:14,631 --> 00:48:16,029
No talking.

587
00:48:16,131 --> 00:48:17,801
We're playing
the silent game

588
00:48:17,903 --> 00:48:20,235
- and you wanna win, right?
- Yeah.

589
00:48:25,137 --> 00:48:27,407
I want my crayons.

590
00:48:28,842 --> 00:48:32,412
- You're gonna lose
if you say anything.
- [quietly] Okay.

591
00:48:38,418 --> 00:48:39,985
[Brenda on phone]
I don't know...

592
00:48:40,087 --> 00:48:41,454
[Analee sneezes loudly]

593
00:48:42,355 --> 00:48:45,128
I found it
unpacking their clothes.

594
00:48:47,165 --> 00:48:50,628
I get the feeling
they're in some kind
of trouble.

595
00:48:52,297 --> 00:48:54,771
[breathing heavily] Okay.

596
00:48:54,873 --> 00:48:57,437
Okay, listen to me,
baby girl.

597
00:48:58,743 --> 00:49:01,206
Mommy messed up,
okay?

598
00:49:01,308 --> 00:49:04,947
I messed up really bad.
Big mistake.

599
00:49:05,049 --> 00:49:07,818
But you wanna stay
with Mommy, right?

600
00:49:07,920 --> 00:49:10,315
'Cause I really want
to stay with you

601
00:49:10,417 --> 00:49:12,490
and, if we're gonna
stay together,

602
00:49:12,592 --> 00:49:15,018
we have to go right now.

603
00:49:15,120 --> 00:49:18,990
And you have to do exactly
what I'm about to tell you
to do, okay?

604
00:49:19,092 --> 00:49:20,427
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

605
00:49:22,966 --> 00:49:25,201
[suspenseful music playing]

606
00:49:32,241 --> 00:49:34,243
[Analee whispering]
Can we go yet?

607
00:49:35,448 --> 00:49:36,674
[Maben] Okay.

608
00:49:38,176 --> 00:49:41,184
Okay. Go. Go!

609
00:50:24,992 --> 00:50:26,724
[phone ringing]

610
00:50:30,965 --> 00:50:32,400
[Brenda] Hello?

611
00:50:34,102 --> 00:50:36,536
Wait. Where's Analee?

612
00:50:37,974 --> 00:50:40,144
She's not in the room?

613
00:50:41,878 --> 00:50:43,543
Is the mother back?

614
00:50:50,887 --> 00:50:53,149
[distant clattering]

615
00:50:53,251 --> 00:50:55,159
[door opens]

616
00:50:56,990 --> 00:50:58,228
Hello?

617
00:51:01,867 --> 00:51:03,827
Analee, is that you,
honey?

618
00:51:05,769 --> 00:51:07,369
Is anyone there?

619
00:51:08,840 --> 00:51:11,868
[dramatic music playing]

620
00:51:15,780 --> 00:51:17,676
[grunting, panting]

621
00:51:38,131 --> 00:51:39,401
[lighter clicks]

622
00:52:04,492 --> 00:52:06,593
- [Maben] Don't move.
- [gun clicks]

623
00:52:08,734 --> 00:52:10,366
Get in the truck.

624
00:52:12,234 --> 00:52:14,068
Will you get
in the truck?

625
00:52:14,170 --> 00:52:16,099
- All right?
- I'm goin'.

626
00:52:16,202 --> 00:52:17,637
Hurry up.

627
00:52:38,128 --> 00:52:40,258
Okay, just turn on
the car.

628
00:52:40,360 --> 00:52:42,493
Turn on the car
and drive!

629
00:52:42,595 --> 00:52:44,629
- [engine turns over]
- Where?

630
00:52:44,732 --> 00:52:49,001
Just-just go.
Get a-- Get away
from the lights.

631
00:52:49,103 --> 00:52:50,670
North, go North.

632
00:52:55,111 --> 00:52:56,407
- Mama?
- Yeah, baby.

633
00:52:56,509 --> 00:52:58,909
I gotta pee
really badly.

634
00:53:00,746 --> 00:53:03,014
Okay, how bad
do you have to pee?

635
00:53:03,117 --> 00:53:07,122
- Really badly.
Can we stop, please?
- We'll find her a place.

636
00:53:07,224 --> 00:53:09,524
I got a place
for you to pee.

637
00:53:11,130 --> 00:53:13,896
And you can lower
that pistol as well.

638
00:53:13,998 --> 00:53:15,330
Lot of potholes out here,

639
00:53:15,432 --> 00:53:16,993
don't need you
accidentally shooting me.

640
00:53:17,095 --> 00:53:19,663
Didn't come this far
to have it read
on my tombstone

641
00:53:19,765 --> 00:53:21,998
"Accidentally shot
by some woman."

642
00:53:25,639 --> 00:53:28,004
If I shoot you,
it's not an accident.

643
00:53:31,245 --> 00:53:34,014
Tsk. Understood.

644
00:53:34,116 --> 00:53:36,753
[vehicle pulls over]

645
00:53:36,855 --> 00:53:38,322
[sets parking brake]

646
00:53:39,785 --> 00:53:43,089
You hurry up. Okay?
Go pee fast--

647
00:53:43,191 --> 00:53:46,062
Hey!
No. No!

648
00:53:46,164 --> 00:53:47,426
Fucking give that
back to me.

649
00:53:47,528 --> 00:53:49,927
Oh, I think
I'll hold on to that.

650
00:53:51,132 --> 00:53:52,699
[gun clicking]

651
00:53:58,404 --> 00:54:00,311
This ain't your gun.

652
00:54:03,347 --> 00:54:05,578
Can you just
give me back that gun?

653
00:54:05,680 --> 00:54:07,681
You can empty it out,
I don't care, just--

654
00:54:08,880 --> 00:54:11,021
- Just give it back to me.
- I will...

655
00:54:11,123 --> 00:54:13,684
when you tell me
who it belongs to.

656
00:54:13,786 --> 00:54:16,019
- [Maben sighs]
- [rain pattering]

657
00:54:21,967 --> 00:54:23,862
I tried to fix all this...

658
00:54:26,202 --> 00:54:28,906
before it even started.

659
00:54:29,008 --> 00:54:31,034
You know,
I went down...

660
00:54:32,711 --> 00:54:35,277
to this place in New Orleans
when I found out
I was pregnant.

661
00:54:35,379 --> 00:54:37,612
I thought it was
the right thing to do.

662
00:54:39,114 --> 00:54:40,681
Maybe it was.

663
00:54:45,923 --> 00:54:47,083
But as I--

664
00:54:48,658 --> 00:54:51,429
As I was sittin' there,
in that room, waiting,

665
00:54:51,531 --> 00:54:53,724
and I don't know,
I just started thinking
that, you know,

666
00:54:53,826 --> 00:54:56,763
maybe everything
was going to be okay.

667
00:54:58,668 --> 00:55:01,372
[voice breaking] I've tried
so fucking hard...

668
00:55:02,972 --> 00:55:06,410
You know, I actually
didn't even know a person
could, uh...

669
00:55:08,309 --> 00:55:10,679
could try that hard.

670
00:55:10,781 --> 00:55:15,512
[sniffs] But you know, uh...
[sniffs] nowhere worked out.

671
00:55:15,614 --> 00:55:18,089
Not Shreveport, not...

672
00:55:18,191 --> 00:55:21,755
not Beaumont,
not Lake Charles, and...

673
00:55:25,590 --> 00:55:27,695
I can't feed her.

674
00:55:29,763 --> 00:55:32,403
[weeping] I can't put
clothes on her.

675
00:55:33,737 --> 00:55:37,502
I can't give her
a fucking place to sleep
and now this.

676
00:55:37,604 --> 00:55:40,209
So yeah... [sniffles] Uh...

677
00:55:40,311 --> 00:55:44,780
If you could just
leave us here...

678
00:55:44,883 --> 00:55:46,477
Please...

679
00:55:46,579 --> 00:55:48,683
And what about
your family?

680
00:55:49,619 --> 00:55:53,655
What about her daddy?
What about your mama?

681
00:55:55,461 --> 00:55:58,025
[smacks lips]
Not everybody
has somebody.

682
00:55:58,127 --> 00:56:00,156
[rain pattering]

683
00:56:06,564 --> 00:56:08,703
So where to now?

684
00:56:11,140 --> 00:56:12,140
[stammers]

685
00:56:12,242 --> 00:56:13,837
I'll make you a promise.

686
00:56:13,939 --> 00:56:18,610
I'll drive you anywhere,
within reason.

687
00:56:18,712 --> 00:56:21,815
But we're gonna
take a rest tonight.

688
00:56:22,985 --> 00:56:23,883
Okay?

689
00:56:32,859 --> 00:56:34,795
[Maben]<i> I knew</i>
<i>it wasn't gonna end.</i>

690
00:56:36,499 --> 00:56:40,202
<i>All I could see</i>
<i>was her face.</i>

691
00:56:40,304 --> 00:56:41,869
Thinking that I'd left her,

692
00:56:41,971 --> 00:56:45,201
thinking that nobody
in the whole world
cared about her.

693
00:56:49,546 --> 00:56:51,744
So I stole his gun
and I shot him.

694
00:56:51,847 --> 00:56:54,144
I shot him
until he wasn't movin'
no more.

695
00:57:03,362 --> 00:57:05,595
But you don't look
like a killer to me.

696
00:57:07,698 --> 00:57:10,798
I've seen plenty,
I know what they look like.

697
00:57:13,169 --> 00:57:14,731
[fire crackling]

698
00:57:14,833 --> 00:57:16,573
[cigarette rustling in box]

699
00:57:23,174 --> 00:57:26,616
Why are you holdin' on
to that gun, anyway?

700
00:57:28,013 --> 00:57:30,246
You know that damn thing
gon' bury you.

701
00:57:32,450 --> 00:57:36,021
If there's one thing
in the world
that could bury you...

702
00:57:37,792 --> 00:57:40,025
would you wanna know
where it was?

703
00:57:43,398 --> 00:57:45,030
What's your name?

704
00:57:55,206 --> 00:57:57,977
- [insects chirping]
- [soft music playing]

705
00:58:02,120 --> 00:58:03,851
[grunting softly]

706
00:58:06,584 --> 00:58:08,053
Got her?

707
00:58:09,221 --> 00:58:11,991
You guys just sleep in here.
I'll take the back.

708
00:58:19,465 --> 00:58:20,934
Maben.

709
00:58:25,539 --> 00:58:27,270
My name's Maben.

710
00:58:33,150 --> 00:58:34,178
I'm Russell.

711
00:58:59,142 --> 00:59:00,875
Maben...

712
00:59:04,810 --> 00:59:07,277
You gotta be kiddin' me.

713
00:59:13,354 --> 00:59:15,087
Cody?

714
00:59:17,425 --> 00:59:19,322
Cody, boy.

715
00:59:21,464 --> 00:59:25,163
Big papa's home.
Big--

716
00:59:26,401 --> 00:59:27,566
Hey. Hey, I--

717
00:59:27,668 --> 00:59:29,135
Look, I know
that it's--

718
00:59:29,237 --> 00:59:31,708
- You're not supposed
to be here.
- [stammering] I-I know.

719
00:59:31,810 --> 00:59:33,771
- I know, I know.
- Go on, Larry.
Go on. Come on.

720
00:59:33,873 --> 00:59:36,842
Look, look,
is-is he here?

721
00:59:36,944 --> 00:59:40,146
- Is Cody here?
- 'Course he's here.

722
00:59:40,248 --> 00:59:42,819
- Could I-could I see him
for a minute?
- Oh, Larry.

723
00:59:42,921 --> 00:59:45,355
- It's the middle of the night.
- Baby, baby, please, please.

724
00:59:45,457 --> 00:59:46,719
No, it's the middle
of the night.

725
00:59:46,821 --> 00:59:48,351
I just wanna see him
for a minute.

726
00:59:50,523 --> 00:59:52,229
[sighs]

727
00:59:52,331 --> 00:59:54,027
I see you've been drinking.

728
00:59:56,831 --> 00:59:59,263
Yeah. Yeah,
I've been drinking.

729
01:00:07,039 --> 01:00:09,711
I just got
one question, okay?

730
01:00:09,813 --> 01:00:12,881
Is-is-is he still
playing Little League?

731
01:00:14,347 --> 01:00:18,083
- [sighs]
- Is he still playing?
Is he-is he--

732
01:00:18,185 --> 01:00:20,954
Is he swinging the bat
like his Daddy showed him?

733
01:00:21,056 --> 01:00:24,653
[sobbing] He's too big
for Little League, Larry!

734
01:00:24,756 --> 01:00:26,022
Goddammit!

735
01:00:26,124 --> 01:00:28,531
You'd know that
if you saw him.

736
01:00:28,633 --> 01:00:30,694
Well, fuck!
You won't let me see him.

737
01:00:30,796 --> 01:00:33,670
That ain't fuckin' fair!
What are you talking about,
"if I saw him"?

738
01:00:33,772 --> 01:00:35,638
I've been tryin' to see him,
that's why I'm here!

739
01:00:35,740 --> 01:00:38,434
Get sober
and you can see
your son.

740
01:00:38,536 --> 01:00:41,103
- That's what I said.
- [yelling] I'm fuckin' trying!

741
01:00:41,205 --> 01:00:42,944
- Not hard enough!
