01:31:22,516 --> 01:31:24,278
and here I go,
leaving her.

1216
01:31:26,919 --> 01:31:28,917
Every single fuckin' thing
I've done wrong,

1217
01:31:29,019 --> 01:31:32,055
I've brought down
on that little girl.

1218
01:31:32,157 --> 01:31:35,029
Hey, life's a whirlwind.
We're all caught up in it.

1219
01:31:35,131 --> 01:31:36,357
You're a good mama.

1220
01:31:36,459 --> 01:31:38,926
Hell, anyone can see how much
you love that little girl,

1221
01:31:39,028 --> 01:31:40,702
you love her so bad,
it hurts.

1222
01:31:40,804 --> 01:31:43,365
And if it didn't hurt,
you wouldn't be
doing it right.

1223
01:31:43,468 --> 01:31:46,542
That hurt never goes away,
it doesn't matter
how old they get.

1224
01:31:48,676 --> 01:31:51,844
Just do the best you can
for right now,

1225
01:31:51,946 --> 01:31:54,308
and you don't worry
about tomorrow
until it comes.

1226
01:31:58,949 --> 01:32:00,589
You're doing
the right thing.

1227
01:32:03,157 --> 01:32:04,186
[sighs]

1228
01:32:07,727 --> 01:32:10,060
- Take care of her.
- Oh, yeah.

1229
01:32:12,233 --> 01:32:13,363
[Mitchell] Ahem.

1230
01:32:13,465 --> 01:32:15,230
[Maben sobs]

1231
01:32:19,309 --> 01:32:22,336
[suspenseful music playing]

1232
01:32:38,194 --> 01:32:39,925
[exhales sharply]

1233
01:32:41,890 --> 01:32:44,127
[breathing heavily]

1234
01:32:55,344 --> 01:32:58,746
[car doors open and close]

1235
01:33:00,943 --> 01:33:03,179
[footsteps approaching]

1236
01:33:11,327 --> 01:33:12,353
[light switch clicks]

1237
01:33:32,808 --> 01:33:34,276
Coast's clear.

1238
01:33:35,716 --> 01:33:37,351
I've got everything
ready here.

1239
01:33:37,453 --> 01:33:39,451
Got you a bunch of supplies.

1240
01:33:39,553 --> 01:33:41,320
Can I use your bathroom?

1241
01:33:41,422 --> 01:33:42,922
Sure, down the hall.

1242
01:33:45,188 --> 01:33:46,959
- [Larry yells]
- [crowbar lands]

1243
01:33:48,361 --> 01:33:49,326
Maben!

1244
01:33:49,428 --> 01:33:51,030
[roars]

1245
01:33:51,132 --> 01:33:54,362
- [dramatic music playing]
- [both grunting and groaning]

1246
01:34:02,909 --> 01:34:05,478
- That's all you've got?
- [Russell] Yeah!

1247
01:34:05,580 --> 01:34:09,017
[grunting and groaning continue]

1248
01:34:09,119 --> 01:34:10,347
Motherfucker!

1249
01:34:10,450 --> 01:34:12,017
[grunting]

1250
01:34:19,555 --> 01:34:23,792
You killed the wrong one.
You ain't fucking perfect.

1251
01:34:23,894 --> 01:34:26,163
You should've killed me.

1252
01:34:29,769 --> 01:34:32,004
[Russell breathing heavily]

1253
01:34:33,936 --> 01:34:35,711
It's over now, boy.

1254
01:34:37,345 --> 01:34:38,714
[Russell groans]

1255
01:34:43,418 --> 01:34:46,249
[breathing heavily]

1256
01:34:46,351 --> 01:34:49,419
I've been waitin'
seven fuckin' years
for this.

1257
01:34:49,522 --> 01:34:50,990
[gunshot]

1258
01:34:53,163 --> 01:34:54,422
[rifle clatters]

1259
01:34:55,528 --> 01:34:56,663
[body thuds]

1260
01:34:56,765 --> 01:34:59,829
- [Larry groaning]
- You okay, son?

1261
01:34:59,931 --> 01:35:01,364
Dammit, Larry,
I'm sorry.

1262
01:35:01,466 --> 01:35:03,830
Why don't you sit down, son?
I'll call you an ambulance.

1263
01:35:03,932 --> 01:35:05,235
[Larry groaning]

1264
01:35:07,276 --> 01:35:08,810
[shotgun cocks]

1265
01:35:14,250 --> 01:35:15,214
[Russell] Maben!

1266
01:35:15,316 --> 01:35:17,481
Maben!

1267
01:35:17,583 --> 01:35:18,912
[shotgun thuds]

1268
01:35:19,014 --> 01:35:20,248
Goddammit, Mitchell!

1269
01:35:20,351 --> 01:35:22,051
I told you to stay
the hell out of this shit.

1270
01:35:22,153 --> 01:35:24,052
- [tires screech]
- You can damn me later.

1271
01:35:24,154 --> 01:35:25,992
We gotta get her
the hell outta here.

1272
01:35:27,292 --> 01:35:29,798
[Mitchell]
Damn, I knew
he'd do something wrong.

1273
01:35:32,862 --> 01:35:34,099
Careful there.

1274
01:35:35,634 --> 01:35:37,172
Be safe, son.

1275
01:35:37,274 --> 01:35:38,366
[Russell] Get home!

1276
01:35:38,468 --> 01:35:40,803
- Get rid
of that fuckin' gun!
- Yeah, yeah.

1277
01:35:40,905 --> 01:35:44,142
[dramatic music playing]

1278
01:35:53,853 --> 01:35:57,089
[extended, insistent honking]

1279
01:36:08,700 --> 01:36:10,102
Come here, boy.

1280
01:36:11,636 --> 01:36:13,105
Cody...

1281
01:36:14,838 --> 01:36:16,570
Cody, boy...

1282
01:36:19,314 --> 01:36:20,445
Cody...

1283
01:36:20,547 --> 01:36:24,318
[yelling] Cody!

1284
01:36:24,420 --> 01:36:27,652
[mumbles indistinct]

1285
01:36:27,754 --> 01:36:29,517
Jesus Christ, Larry...

1286
01:36:30,760 --> 01:36:32,825
- Where is my son?
- What happened to you?

1287
01:36:32,927 --> 01:36:34,521
- Who did this to you?
- Where is he?

1288
01:36:34,623 --> 01:36:36,663
- Larry...
- Mom, what the fuck's
going on?

1289
01:36:36,765 --> 01:36:38,097
- Go call 911!
- Why is he here?

1290
01:36:38,199 --> 01:36:39,667
- Dad, why the fuck
are you here?
- Call 911!

1291
01:36:39,769 --> 01:36:41,962
- Why? What's going on?
- [Larry mumbling]

1292
01:36:42,064 --> 01:36:45,406
- Is he fuckin' bleeding?
Why are you bleeding?
- Go call 911, Cody!

1293
01:36:45,508 --> 01:36:47,202
- He needs help!
- Go call!

1294
01:36:47,304 --> 01:36:50,437
Come here, boy...
Let me touch my son.

1295
01:36:50,539 --> 01:36:52,914
[panting] Larry,
don't move, please. Okay?

1296
01:36:53,016 --> 01:36:55,047
- Try not to move, Larry--
- Get the fuck away from me.

1297
01:36:55,149 --> 01:36:57,113
- Goddammit.
Hey, listen.
- [groaning loudly]

1298
01:36:57,215 --> 01:36:59,821
Stay right there,
okay? Don't move!

1299
01:36:59,923 --> 01:37:04,086
- Imma get you help...
- You all did this to me.

1300
01:37:04,188 --> 01:37:07,621
You all did it.
You all did it.

1301
01:37:09,060 --> 01:37:10,624
- [dog barking]
- [groaning]

1302
01:37:12,963 --> 01:37:15,200
[breathing heavily]

1303
01:37:20,640 --> 01:37:23,104
- [Dana] Hey, you can't go!
- [Cody] Dad,
what are you doing?

1304
01:37:23,206 --> 01:37:24,405
Dad, stop!
Where are you going?

1305
01:37:24,507 --> 01:37:27,341
You can't drive like that,
Larry! Come on!

1306
01:37:27,443 --> 01:37:30,845
Oh, shit, he's driving!
He's driving!

1307
01:37:30,947 --> 01:37:33,484
Please hurry!

1308
01:37:33,586 --> 01:37:34,956
Help!

1309
01:37:35,952 --> 01:37:37,557
Somebody help!

1310
01:37:37,659 --> 01:37:40,896
[dramatic music playing]

1311
01:37:42,795 --> 01:37:45,032
Somebody help us!

1312
01:37:48,031 --> 01:37:51,135
Maben... we're here.

1313
01:37:51,238 --> 01:37:53,906
- [nurse] What happened?
- She-- she fell. She...

1314
01:37:54,008 --> 01:37:55,738
hit her head.
Her head flipped back.

1315
01:37:55,840 --> 01:37:58,078
[mumbles, pants]

1316
01:38:04,680 --> 01:38:08,121
- [dramatic music continues]
- [sirens wailing]

1317
01:38:10,888 --> 01:38:13,456
[yelling]

1318
01:38:17,367 --> 01:38:20,397
[music swells]

1319
01:38:30,743 --> 01:38:33,982
[truck crashes]

1320
01:38:42,623 --> 01:38:44,926
[phones ringing]

1321
01:38:45,028 --> 01:38:47,160
I heard your address
on the wire. Shots fired?

1322
01:38:48,356 --> 01:38:49,992
Hell yeah,
shots fired.

1323
01:38:50,094 --> 01:38:51,494
What the hell happened?

1324
01:38:54,871 --> 01:38:58,505
Walked in my place,
Larry was there.

1325
01:38:58,607 --> 01:38:59,833
Had a woman with me,

1326
01:38:59,935 --> 01:39:02,939
he hit her over the head
with a crowbar thinkin'
it was me.

1327
01:39:03,041 --> 01:39:04,174
Him and I got into it,

1328
01:39:04,276 --> 01:39:07,345
I got ahold of my rifle
and I shot 'im.

1329
01:39:08,881 --> 01:39:10,282
Who is she, Russ?

1330
01:39:11,987 --> 01:39:14,385
You know goddamn well
who she is.

1331
01:39:20,025 --> 01:39:22,259
Russ, you gotta tell me.

1332
01:39:22,361 --> 01:39:24,863
What the hell you got
to do with all this?

1333
01:39:24,965 --> 01:39:27,200
[woman over P.A. indistinct]

1334
01:39:28,398 --> 01:39:30,633
I'll explain
everything to you.

1335
01:39:31,870 --> 01:39:34,568
You gotta promise me
you ain't gonna listen to me
like a lawman.

1336
01:39:34,670 --> 01:39:36,306
What do you want me
to listen to you like?

1337
01:39:36,409 --> 01:39:38,607
I want you to listen to me
like you're you...

1338
01:39:40,076 --> 01:39:41,511
and I'm me.

1339
01:39:47,622 --> 01:39:49,354
Okay. Okay.

1340
01:39:53,256 --> 01:39:55,492
[indistinct radio chatter]

1341
01:39:59,029 --> 01:40:01,801
[Russell]<i> The pistol</i>
<i>you're looking for</i>
<i>is over in the lake.</i>

1342
01:40:01,903 --> 01:40:03,567
<i>Same one Maben held on me</i>

1343
01:40:03,669 --> 01:40:06,735
<i>when I walked out</i>
<i>of the Armadillo</i>
<i>a few nights ago.</i>

1344
01:40:06,837 --> 01:40:10,804
<i>That's when she got to talkin'</i>
<i>about how some deputy</i>

1345
01:40:10,906 --> 01:40:13,981
<i>made her do everything</i>
<i>that he wanted her to do,</i>

1346
01:40:14,084 --> 01:40:15,980
<i>even called</i>
<i>his goddamned friends along</i>

1347
01:40:16,083 --> 01:40:17,845
<i>to come have a go at her too.</i>

1348
01:40:17,947 --> 01:40:20,680
Next thing she knew,
he was down, dead,
and she kept on runnin',

1349
01:40:20,782 --> 01:40:23,223
kept on runnin' straight
until she ran into me.

1350
01:40:24,791 --> 01:40:27,524
Why the hell didn't you
and her just both
come straight to me?

1351
01:40:29,397 --> 01:40:32,331
Nobody would've believed her
and you know it, Boyd.

1352
01:40:35,231 --> 01:40:36,732
She'da lost the kid.

1353
01:40:36,834 --> 01:40:40,273
And I'll be goddamned,
but I believe
everything she says.

1354
01:40:42,475 --> 01:40:44,207
My road's the road
that brought us all here,

1355
01:40:44,309 --> 01:40:46,343
led by what hand,
I don't know.

1356
01:40:46,446 --> 01:40:49,446
But here we are,
and I ain't lettin' this go.

1357
01:40:49,548 --> 01:40:51,479
Shit, I'm only telling you
all this so you know

1358
01:40:51,581 --> 01:40:53,888
when I ask you
just leave her alone.

1359
01:40:53,990 --> 01:40:55,849
I ain't tellin' you,
I'm askin' you.

1360
01:40:58,661 --> 01:41:00,293
Just let it fall.

1361
01:41:01,531 --> 01:41:02,790
Let it fall?

1362
01:41:04,359 --> 01:41:06,726
Just let it fall.

1363
01:41:06,829 --> 01:41:09,599
Do you know
who's at my house
right now?

1364
01:41:12,069 --> 01:41:13,838
Yes, I do.

1365
01:41:13,940 --> 01:41:16,472
And do you know what the boys
at Parchman would do
to a sheriff's deputy?

1366
01:41:16,574 --> 01:41:19,246
Huh? It'd make your time
look like summer camp.

1367
01:41:27,516 --> 01:41:29,751
Where's the proof,
Russell?

1368
01:41:38,196 --> 01:41:40,135
[vehicle approaching]

1369
01:41:50,338 --> 01:41:51,371
[casings clink]

1370
01:41:51,473 --> 01:41:54,710
[dramatic music playing]

1371
01:42:04,055 --> 01:42:05,358
[whistles]

1372
01:42:12,694 --> 01:42:14,466
What does that
look like to you?

1373
01:42:17,904 --> 01:42:20,934
[music swells]

1374
01:42:50,532 --> 01:42:53,769
[pensive music playing]

1375
01:42:59,110 --> 01:43:00,677
[muted dialogue]

1376
01:43:15,624 --> 01:43:18,830
[Maben]<i> The days are slow.</i>

1377
01:43:18,932 --> 01:43:21,528
<i>They get that way</i>
<i>when you're waiting</i>
<i>on something to happen</i>

1378
01:43:21,630 --> 01:43:23,568
<i>that you hope never will.</i>

1379
01:43:28,444 --> 01:43:31,345
<i>You can't help but wonder</i>
<i>if today is the day...</i>

1380
01:43:33,147 --> 01:43:35,248
<i>they'll be sittin' there,</i>

1381
01:43:35,350 --> 01:43:38,217
<i>then here they come,</i>
<i>over that hill,</i>

1382
01:43:38,319 --> 01:43:42,483
<i>down the driveway,</i>
<i>lights flashing,</i>

1383
01:43:42,586 --> 01:43:44,820
<i>sirens calling out your name.</i>

1384
01:43:46,788 --> 01:43:48,896
<i>Russell told me</i>
<i>about this dream</i>

1385
01:43:48,998 --> 01:43:51,825
<i>of being back on the inside,</i>

1386
01:43:51,927 --> 01:43:54,434
<i>about how the light</i>
<i>was always grey,</i>

1387
01:43:55,669 --> 01:43:58,405
<i>and there was always</i>
<i>this voice calling out...</i>

1388
01:44:00,502 --> 01:44:02,208
<i>Just some cry,</i>

1389
01:44:02,310 --> 01:44:04,543
<i>echoing through</i>
<i>an empty prison...</i>

1390
01:44:07,109 --> 01:44:09,713
<i>and he never knew</i>
<i>what he was supposed to do.</i>

1391
01:44:11,452 --> 01:44:14,014
<i>If he was supposed</i>
<i>to be helping it, or...</i>

1392
01:44:15,387 --> 01:44:17,391
<i>if it was there to help him.</i>

1393
01:44:20,356 --> 01:44:21,896
[Analee giggles]

1394
01:44:21,998 --> 01:44:24,027
[Mabel speaks indistinctly]

1395
01:44:24,129 --> 01:44:25,465
[Analee screams]

1396
01:44:25,567 --> 01:44:27,863
<i>Sometimes I think it was me</i>
<i>he was hearing...</i>

1397
01:44:30,434 --> 01:44:33,671
[soft music continues]

1398
01:44:39,076 --> 01:44:42,075
<i>I don't guess there's no way</i>
<i>of knowing what's coming.</i>

1399
01:44:45,715 --> 01:44:48,950
<i>Never has been.</i>
<i>Never will be.</i>

1400
01:44:52,059 --> 01:44:53,493
<i>But, for once,</i>

1401
01:44:54,864 --> 01:44:56,023
<i>I'm not afraid.</i>

1402
01:45:09,945 --> 01:45:11,038
[Analee giggling]

1403
01:45:19,287 --> 01:45:22,184
- [laughing]
- [muted dialogue]

1404
01:45:22,286 --> 01:45:24,524
[birds chirping]

1405
01:45:27,756 --> 01:45:29,991
<i>And when the daylight fades,</i>

1406
01:45:31,830 --> 01:45:34,600
<i>and it seems okay</i>
<i>to breathe a little...</i>

1407
01:45:39,007 --> 01:45:40,672
<i>that low light</i>

1408
01:45:41,440 --> 01:45:44,044
<i>gives her this long shadow,</i>

1409
01:45:44,147 --> 01:45:46,381
<i>like her arms are spread out.</i>

1410
01:45:48,281 --> 01:45:49,810
<i>As if she's saying,</i>

1411
01:45:49,912 --> 01:45:53,018
<i>"Come here</i>
<i>and let me hold you..."</i>

1412
01:45:53,120 --> 01:45:56,017
[indistinct chatter]

1413
01:45:57,124 --> 01:45:58,459
<i>I don't know...</i>

1414
01:45:58,561 --> 01:46:01,493
- [laughing]
- Get-- get up! Get up!
Here, stand up.

1415
01:46:01,596 --> 01:46:04,423
<i>Maybe there is</i>
<i>such a thing as a miracle.</i>

1416
01:46:04,526 --> 01:46:06,665
I got you.

1417
01:46:17,773 --> 01:46:20,008
<i>All I know for certain...</i>

1418
01:46:23,545 --> 01:46:25,112
<i>she's mine.</i>

1419
01:46:33,027 --> 01:46:34,121
[music ends]

1420
01:46:37,500 --> 01:46:39,731
["Desperation Road"
by Garrett Hedlund begins]

1421
01:46:48,042 --> 01:46:51,072
[song continues]

1422
01:48:58,337 --> 01:49:01,576
[song ends]

1423
01:49:03,809 --> 01:49:07,043
["Wolves"
by Sanders Bohlke begins]

1424
01:50:10,442 --> 01:50:13,681
[song continues]

1425
01:51:56,449 --> 01:51:57,983
[song ends]

